data.description: Location, location, location!!!! This well kept historic and charming cottage is located on a quiet street off Kings St and Rutledge Ave. It is only a block from Hampton Park, which includes great trails/tracks for walking, biking, jogging, picnicking, nature walks, playgrounds, golf cart rides, beautiful oaks, and enjoying the beauty of our low country.  This cottage was built in 1920, has an open floor plan, an original fireplace for decor, bead board ceilings, ceramic tile bath, hard wood flooring, as well as off and on street parking.  For outdoor living, enjoy grilling out on the patio within the fenced yard and enjoying friends. Walk to many popular, top rated restaurants, bars, & coffee shops!  It is minutes to the Citadel, close to MUSC, Chas hospitals, and the RiverDogs Stadium.Flood insurance is not required.   Property was rezoned in 2021 to an X zone.   No HOA.   Taxes are for our current year 2023.  Off street driveway for parking and street parking is allowed.
